-- Buana Listya, Bumi Serpong, Krakatau: Indonesia Equity Preview
-- B y   B e r n i   M o e s t a f a
-- 2012-03-15T01:38:35Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-15/buana-listya-bumi-serpong-krakatau-indonesia-equity-preview.html
Shares of the following companies
may have  unusual  moves in  Indonesian trading . Stock symbols are
in parentheses, and share prices are as of the previous close.  The  Jakarta Composite index  rose 1.1 percent to 4,054.33.  PT Buana Listya Tama (BULL)  (BULL IJ): Units of  PT Berlian Laju
Tanker (BLTA) , Indonesia’s largest shipping company by market value,
sought protection from creditors in the  U.S. Bankruptcy Court  in
Manhattan under Chapter 15 of the bankruptcy code, which puts on
hold claims while a company reorganizes outside the U.S. Berlian
said Jan. 26 it has temporarily ceased repayments on loans,
bonds and ship leases and on similar debt of its subsidiaries
save for Buana Listya. Buana Listya was unchanged at 67 rupiah.  PT Bumi Serpong Damai (BSDE)  : The property developer’s
2011 net income more than doubled to 840.8 billion rupiah ($91.2
million), beating the 753.4 billion rupiah mean estimate of 14
analysts in a Bloomberg News survey. Bumi Serpong slipped 0.8
percent to 1,210 rupiah.  PT Krakatau Steel (KRAS)  : Net income at Indonesia’s
biggest steel producer slid to 1.03 trillion rupiah from 1.06
trillion rupiah a year earlier, the company said in a statement
published in  Bisnis Indonesia . The mean estimate for net income
was 825.7 billion rupiah, according to three analysts in a
Bloomberg News survey. Krakatau Steel advanced 4.6 percent to
920 rupiah.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Berni Moestafa in Jakarta at 
 bmoestafa@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
